Type 1 Family Weekenders offer a unique three-day experience for children and
young people to enjoy activities away from their parents, often for the first
Joining us as a volunteer means you’ll be helping children, young people and
their families get the most out of the event. They’ll leave feeling supported,
more confident with their diabetes management, having made friends and had
* You’ll make a real difference to the lives of children and their families living with type 1 diabetes
* You’ll take part in a unique and unforgettable experience
* You'll develop your team working skills with a fantastic group of people
We explain everything you need to know about volunteering at a Family
> ### "I love volunteering. It’s very rewarding sharing my experience of
> living with type 1 with others and knowing that I'm helping them."
Read the role description for more information (PDF)
We welcome volunteers with a range of experience and backgrounds. If you’ve
worked with children before that’s great, but if you haven’t, please don’t let
We value enthusiasm, a sense of fun, ability to work as part of a team and
most importantly ability to act responsibly and a genuine desire to help
empower children and their families living with type 1 diabetes. Prior
knowledge of type 1 diabetes is helpful. Most of our general volunteers have
type 1 diabetes themselves, or have a family member or close friend with type
> ### "I enjoy spending time with other diabetics like myself, be it adults
> and children. It’s really fulfilling seeing the children grow throughout
